content.problem:
Two chords intersect inside a circle. One chord is divided into 
segments of 4 and 6. The other chord is divided into segments of 
3 and $x$. Find $x$.

center
tikzpicture[scale=1.2]
 (0,0) circle (1.5);

 (A) at (150:1.5);
 (B) at (-30:1.5);
 (C) at (210:1.5);
 (D) at (60:1.5);
 (P) at (intersection of A–B and C–D);

 (A) – (B);
 (C) – (D);

 ll[AtlasTeal] (A) circle (2pt) node[above left] {$A$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (B) circle (2pt) node[right] {$B$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (C) circle (2pt) node[below left] {$C$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (D) circle (2pt) node[above right] {$D$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (P) circle (2pt) node[below] {$P$};

 at (-0.6,0.3) {$4$};
 at (0.4,-0.1) {$6$};
 at (-0.5,-0.4) {$3$};
 at (0.1,0.4) {$x$};
tikzpicture
