content.problem:
From external point $P$, two secants are drawn to a circle. One 
secant has an external segment of 4 and passes through the circle 
with an internal segment (chord) of 6. The other secant has an 
external segment of 3. Find the whole length of the second secant.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.7]
 (0,0) circle (2);

 (P) at (-4,0);
 (A) at (-2,0);
 (B) at (2,0);
 (C) at (-1.6,1.2);
 (D) at (1.2,-1.6);

 (P) – (B);
 (P) – (D);

 ll[AtlasTeal] (P) circle (3pt) node[left] {$P$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (A) circle (3pt) node[above] {$A$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (B) circle (3pt) node[right] {$B$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (C) circle (3pt) node[above] {$C$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (D) circle (3pt) node[below right] {$D$};

 at (-3,0) {$4$};
 at (0,0) {$6$};
 at (-2.8,0.6) {$3$};
tikzpicture
center
